<BODY text="006400" bgcolor="fff8dc">
<H1 id="center"><img src="./images/kagiana1.jpg" alt="KAGIANA" width="60" height="45" border="0" hspace="12"> KAGIANA</H1>
<h5 align="right"><A HREF="indexjpn.html">Japanese version is here</A></h5><br>
<h4 id="center">Renewed at July 29, 2009; Updated at November 12,2008</h4><br>
<h4 id="center">Here is a portal site of the 
<font color="maroon"><b>KAGIANA</b></font> tool to retrieve 
<font color="maroon">genomic information</font> and 
<font color="maroon">co-expressed genes</font> in <font color="maroon">Arabidopsis</font>.</h4>
<h3>Renewed using the <font size="5"><a href="http://arabidopsis.org/">TAIR9</a></font> dataset.</h3>
<h3>Gene Ontology data have been modified !</h3>
<h3>Interconnected to <a href="./cop/index.html">
<img src="./images/confeitopinkround2.gif" alt="CoP Home" width="20" height="20" border="0">
<font color="darkgreen" size="5"><b>CoP</b> </font></a><font size="1">(upgraded from CoexProcess)</font></h3>
<h4><font color="maroon"><b>Attention !</b></font> The 'Data' sheet has been reconstructed in the renewal. 
The direct links to public databases in the 'Selected_Link' sheet have been modified.</h4>
<br><br>
<h3>Download</h3>
<ul>
<li><a href="./cgi-bin/kagiana.cgi?version=e">
<b>KAGIANA without macro programs</b> <font size="1">(KAGIANA0906e.xls)</font></a>, <i>released !</i></li><br><br>
<li><b>KAGIANA with macro programs</b> <font size="1">(KAGIANA0906m.xls)</font>, <i>coming soon</i></li><br><br>
<!--
<li><a href="./cgi-bin/kagiana.cgi?version=m">
<b>KAGIANA with macro programs</b> <font size="1">(KAGIANA0906m.xls)</font></a>, <i>coming soon</i></li><br><br>
-->
<li><a href="./cgi-bin/kagiana.cgi?version=8">
<b>KAGIANA published in 2008</b> <font size="1">(KAGIANA0806.xls)</font></a>, <i>using the TAIR8 dataset</i></li><br><br>
<li><a href="./cgi-bin/kagiana.cgi?version=j">
<b>KAGIANA without macro programs in Japanese</b> <font size="1">(KAGIANA0906j.xls)</font></a>, <i>released !</i></li><br><br>
</ul>

<h4>The password to extract the ZIP files : <b>nedo</b></h4>
<h4>For <b>Macintosh</b> users, it is recommended to use a software to uncompress a ZIP file with a password 
such as <a href="https://www.act2.com/download/freeware/stuffit/">StuffIt Expander</a>.</h4>
<h4>For <b>Excel 2007 or later </b> users, 
it is recommended to put this tool in a responsible folder to validate the macro programs for the following functions.</h4><br>

<h3>Available macro programs (coming soon for Windows users only)</h3>
<ul>
<li>Retrieval of co-expressed genes using the 
<b><font size="3" color="darkgreen">Confeito</font></b> algorithm for plant co-expression analysis</li>
<li>Depiction of expression profiles of multiple genes</li>
<li>Depiction of a pie chart of frequency of Gene Ontology terms</li>
<li>Download of an expression profile of each gene from the 
<a href="http://atted.jp">ATTED-II</a> database</li>
</ul><br>

<h3>Modifying macro programs</h3>
<ul>
<li>Depiction of a co-expression network</li>
</ul>

<h4>The older versions are <a href="http://pmnedo.kazusa.or.jp/kagiana/kagiana/index.html">here</a>.</h4><br>

<h3>Correlation data files</h3>
<ul>
<li><a href="./corfiles/np4.zip">Correlation coefficient of +0.4 or higher (54.7MB)</a></li>
<li><a href="./corfiles/np5.zip">Correlation coefficient of +0.5 or higher (21.7MB)</a></li>
<li><a href="./corfiles/np6.zip">Correlation coefficient of +0.6 or higher (8.5MB)</a></li>
<li><a href="./corfiles/np7to9.zip">Correlation coefficient of +0.7 or higher </a></li>
</ul>
<h5>Password for extraction of ZIP files : <b>nedo</b></h5>
<h5>These correlation data are provided by Dr. Obayashi, the administrator of the 
<a href="http://www.atted.bio.titech.ac.jp/">ATTED-II</a>.</h5>
<br>

<h3>Publication</h3>
<ul>
<li>Bioinformatics tools to discover co-expressed genes in plants. 
Ogata, Y., Sakurai, N., Provart, N.J., Steinhauser, D., Krall, L. 
<i>In The handbook of Plant Functional Genomics Concepts and Protocols</i>, edited by Kahl, G. and Meksem, K. 
pp. 309-335, WILEY-VCH Verlag. GmbH & Co. KGaA, Weinheim (2008)</li><br><br>
<li><a href="http://pcp.oxfordjournals.org/cgi/content/full/50/1/173">
KAGIANA: an Excel-based tool for retrieving summary information on <i>Arabidopsis</i> genes. 
Ogata, Y., Sakurai, N., Aoki, K., Suzuki, H., Okazaki, K., Saito, K., Shibata, D. 
<i>Plant and Cell Physiology</i>, 50(1):173-177 (2009)</a></li>
</ul><br>

<h3>Links</h3>
<h4><b>Plant co-expression</b></h4>
<ul>
<li><a href="http://atted.jp/"><b>ATTED-II</b></a> 
for analyzing Arabidopsis co-expressed genes and predicting cis-elements</li>
<br><br>
<li><a href="http://webs2.kazusa.or.jp/kagiana/cop/">
The <b><i>CoP</i></b></a> 
for plant co-expressed biological processes, upgraded from CoexProcess</li>
<br><br>
<li><a href="http://webs2.kazusa.or.jp/kagiana/rnr/">
The <b><i>RnR</i></b></a> 
for predicting the regulation of gene expression and metabolite accumulation in Arabidopsis T87 cultured cells</li>
<br><br>
</ul><br><br>

